# Environment Variables - MongoDB Configuration

## Development

```bash
# MongoDB Atlas Connection String
# Format: mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/database-name
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster0.jh7mffz.mongodb.net/kaptan-lucky-draw

# JWT Secret for token signing (min 32 chars recommended)
JWT_SECRET=replace-with-a-long-random-secret

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=development

# Optional: Redis (for future caching)
# REDIS_URL=redis://localhost:6379
```

## Production

```bash
# MongoDB Atlas Connection String (use environment secret manager)
MONGODB_URI=mongodb+srv://<username>:<password>@cluster0.jh7mffz.mongodb.net/kaptan-lucky-draw-prod

# Strong JWT Secret (use environment secret manager)
JWT_SECRET=<strong-random-32-plus-character-secret>

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=production
```

## Security Notes

1. Add `.env` to `.gitignore`.
2. Use environment secret manager in production.
3. Rotate passwords periodically.
4. Use strong passwords and secrets.

## Verification

Test connection with:
```bash
# In Node.js
import { connectDB } from "@workspace/db-mongoose";
await connectDB();
console.log("Connected!");
```
